### runOnSCC() {#a1b5da54a738562b74b79cf746dd1c01d}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>bool AMDGPUAnnotateKernelFeatures::runOnSCC (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/callgraphscc">CallGraphSCC</a> &amp; SCC)</>}
  labels = {["virtual"]}>
runOnSCC - This method should be implemented by the subclass to perform whatever action is necessary for the specified SCC.

Note that non-recursive (or only self-recursive) functions will have an SCC size of 1, where recursive portions of the call graph will have SCC size &gt; 1.

SCC passes that add or delete functions to the SCC are required to update the SCC list, otherwise stale pointers may be dereferenced.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/amdgpu/amdgpuannotatekernelfeatures-cpp/#l00039">39</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/amdgpu/amdgpuannotatekernelfeatures-cpp">AMDGPUAnnotateKernelFeatures.cpp</a>.
